The paper deals with optimization problems in computer science, specifically in the area of robust optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve algorithms for set cover, Steiner tree, facility location, minimum-cut, and multicut problems. These are all topics that fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with game theory (cs.GT) in the context of worst-case scenarios, and computational geometry (cs.CG) in the context of Steiner trees. The paper involves mathematical programming and optimization (cs.DM) techniques, and the approximation algorithms used in the paper are based on linear programming relaxations and rounding techniques, which are common in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
